## Root Agent

<!--
  Explains the symlink convention. AGENTS.md IS CLAUDE.md (per ADR-055).
  When Claude Code loads CLAUDE.md at session start, it loads this content.
  Editing CLAUDE.md edits this file; editing this file edits CLAUDE.md.
-->

`AGENTS.md` at the project root is a symlink to `CLAUDE.md`. Claude Code reads `CLAUDE.md`
on every session start as global session context. Project-level behavioral directives,
domain expertise reminders, and always-on conventions belong in `CLAUDE.md` — they appear
here by symlink.

